PropertyDefinition.Name: Transmission acoustique
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates the resistance of sound transmission through this object.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Condition - Condition evaluation
PropertyDefinition.Description: Gives the overall condition of a product based on an assessment of the contributions to the overall condition made by the various criteria considered. The meanings given to the values of assessed condition should be agreed and documented by local agreements. For instance, is overall condition measured on a scale of 1 - 10 or by assigning names such as Good, OK, Poor.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Condition - Date of assessment
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates the date on which the overall condition is assessed.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Construction method
PropertyDefinition.Description: Defines whether the concrete element is constructed on site (IN-SITU) or prefabricated (PRECAST).

PropertyDefinition.Name: Documentation
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates the link to the documentation relating to the element.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Guarantee - finishing date of Guarantee
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates the date on which the warranty expires.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Fire Resistance Rating
PropertyDefinition.Description: Also called fire resistance. Describes the ability of a building component to maintain, for a specified period of time, fire stability (R), fire resistance (E), thermal insulation (I) and/or any other required function. In general, the fire resistance classes are expressed as follows: REI t, R t, EI t, E t, S t, where t is the period expressed in minutes.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Flammability rating
PropertyDefinition.Description: Also called "reaction to fire". Determines the way a material reacts when it comes into contact with a heat source. The reaction-to-fire requirements for construction products are described according to the classification (main classes and sub-classes smoke production and flaming droplet formation. formation) from NBN EN 13501-1. Remarks : - the requirements in this respect relate to the final application value (thus taking into account the presence of the of any underlying (flammable) materials).

PropertyDefinition.Name: Fire Exit
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indication whether this object is designed to serve as an exit in the case of fire (TRUE) or not (FALSE). Here it defines an exit door in accordance to the national building code.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Position ArchiCAD - IsExternal
PropertyDefinition.Description: (Archicad only) Indication whether the element is designed for use in the exterior (TRUE) or not (FALSE). If TRUE it is an external element that supports the weather conditions (cold, humidity, rain,...)

PropertyDefinition.Name: Structural Function ArchiCAD - IsLoadBearing
PropertyDefinition.Description: (Archicad only) Indicates whether the object is intended to carry loads (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

PropertyDefinition.Name: Outer shell
PropertyDefinition.Description: Determines whether the element is part of the external envelope of the building (TRUE) or not (FALSE). In other words whether it is an element between the heated volume and the external environment.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Phasing
PropertyDefinition.Description: Determines the phase during which the element is implemented (if the project is carried out in several phases).

PropertyDefinition.Name: Reinforcement
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates the ratio of the reinforcement mass (kg) to the (m³) of the concrete element.

PropertyDefinition.Name: IFC renovation status
PropertyDefinition.Description: (Archicad IFC4 only) Indicates the status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished, "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

PropertyDefinition.Name: Status (Space and Zone)
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates the status of the spaces and zones, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished, "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

PropertyDefinition.Name: Thermal Conductivity
PropertyDefinition.Description: Determines the maximum thermal conductivity (λ-value) of a material, expressed in W/(mK).

PropertyDefinition.Name: Thermal Transmittance
PropertyDefinition.Description: Defines the overall heat transfer coefficient through the wall in the direction of heat flow (all materials included) (U-value).

PropertyDefinition.Name: Work package
PropertyDefinition.Description: Determines the batch in which this element is executed.

PropertyDefinition.Name: BulletProof
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates the resistance of the door against bullet passage (according to STS 53.1)

PropertyDefinition.Name: Glazing - Type (single=1-double=2-triple=3-quadruple=4)
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates the number of glass layers within the frame. E.g. "2" for double glazing.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Glazing - Glazed area ratio
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates the fraction of the glazing area relative to the total area of the frame.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Has Sill External
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates whether the window opening has an external sill (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

PropertyDefinition.Name: Has Sill Internal
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates whether the window opening has an internal sill (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

PropertyDefinition.Name: Window shading - Automatic
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates whether the blackout device is automatic (TRUE) or not (FALSE)

PropertyDefinition.Name: Window shading - Portable
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates whether the blackout device is movable (TRUE) or not (FALSE)

PropertyDefinition.Name: Passage width
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates the net passage width.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Security Rating
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates the resistance of the door to static and dynamic forces and human human attack.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Glazing - Solar transmission
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates the incident solar radiation that is transmitted directly through the glazing.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Type of blackout device
PropertyDefinition.Description: Specifies the type of sun protection the door or window has.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Ventilation gap surface
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates the opening area for air passage (ventilation).

PropertyDefinition.Name: Cabinet with lock (yes/no)
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates whether the file cabinet is lockable (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

PropertyDefinition.Name: Description
PropertyDefinition.Description: Describes the use of the furniture.

PropertyDefinition.Name: physically attached (yes/no)
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates whether the furniture type is 'built in' physically attached to a building or facility (TRUE) or movable (FALSE).

PropertyDefinition.Name: Capacity (volume)
PropertyDefinition.Description: Gives the volumetric capacity of the flush.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Type of manipulation
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates which type of flush the toilet is equipped with.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Is automatic
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates whether flushing is activated automatically after each use or periodically (TRUE) or whether manual flushing is required (FALSE).

PropertyDefinition.Name: Finishing - Ceilings
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates the ceiling finish material if not modelled separately.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Risk factor
PropertyDefinition.Description: Defines, according to local building regulations, the fire risk of the space at several levels of fire hazard.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Finishing - Floors
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates the floor finish material in case it is not modelled separately.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Sprinkling
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates whether the space is sprinkler protected (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

PropertyDefinition.Name: Fire exit space
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates whether this space is an emergency exit (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

PropertyDefinition.Name: Access - accessibility for the disabled
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates whether the element is designed to be accessible to the disabled (TRUE) or not (FALSE). This information is often used to declare the need for disabled access or for special design constraints.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Access - Accessible to the public
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indication whether this space (in case of e.g., a toilet) is designed to serve as a publicly accessible space, e.g., for a public toilet (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

PropertyDefinition.Name: Passage height required
PropertyDefinition.Description: Headroom required for the activity assigned to this space.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Number of expected occupants
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates the number of people required for the activity assigned to this space.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Usage type of space
PropertyDefinition.Description: Defines the intended use of the space.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Finishing - Baseboards
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates the material of the skirting boards if not modelled separately.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Wall finish thickness (requirement)
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates the thickness of the wall finish material if it is not modelled separately.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Finishing - Walls
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates the wall finish material if not modelled separately.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Access control
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates whether the door is equipped with door access control (badge or code, etc.) (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

PropertyDefinition.Name: Motorized opening
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates whether the door is equipped with automatic closing (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

PropertyDefinition.Name: Chimney: Number of pipes
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates the number of the chimney drafts, continuous holes in the chimney through which the air passes.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Opening type
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indication of the requirement of types of window panel operations. Note : although there is an "IfcWindowPanelProperties" property, some softwares do not export sub-component properties. This property has therefore been transferred to the global element.

PropertyDefinition.Name: Place of assembly of the staircase
PropertyDefinition.Description: Indicates where the assembly of the element should take place, either in the factory or on site.
